#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:2
msgid "Drive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:4
msgid ""
"The CryptDrive is used to store and manage documents. For logged in users"
" it is the default landing page on CryptPad. It is also accessible from "
"the other pages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:6
msgid "Clic on the logo at the top-left."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:7
msgid ""
"User menu (avatar at the top-right) > <i class=\"fa fa-hdd-o\"></i> "
"CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:9
msgid "Display"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:11
msgid ""
"Documents in the CryptDrive can be displayed as a <i class=\"fa fa-"
"list\"></i> list or a <i class=\"fa fa-th-large\"></i> grid. To switch "
"between the two, use the button at the right of the CryptDrive toolbar "
"(under the avatar)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:13
msgid ""
"In grid mode, CryptPad can display thumbnails of documents. These can be "
"turned on in the [user settings]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:17
msgid "The CrytpDrive in grid view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:21
msgid "The CryptDrive in list view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:23
msgid "Managing documents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:25
msgid "Folders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:26 ../../user_guide/drive.md:108
#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:128
msgid "{logged in user}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:28
msgid "There are multiple ways to create folders in the CryptDrive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:30
msgid ""
"<i class=\"fa fa-plus\"></i> New in the toolbar > <i class=\"fa fa-"
"folder\"></i> Folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:31
msgid "Right click > <i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i> New folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:32
msgid "Ctrl + e > <i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i> Folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:34
msgid ""
"Once a folder is created, documents can be added to it by dragging them "
"from the CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:36
msgid "To change the color of a folder:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:37
msgid ""
"Right click on the folder > <i class=\"cptools cptools-palette\"></i> "
"Change color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:39
msgid "To share a folder and all of its contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:40
msgid ""
"Right click on the folder > <i class=\"fa fa-share-alt\"></i> Share. The "
"folder will then be converted into a [shared folder]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:42
msgid "Renaming"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:44
msgid ""
"There are two ways to rename documents on CryptPad. One changes the "
"document title for all users, the other changes it only in your "
"CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:46
msgid ""
"To change the title of a documents for all users that have it in their "
"CryptDrive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:47
msgid ""
"Click on the title or the <i class=\"fa fa-pencil\"></i> button in the "
"toolbar of the document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:48
msgid "Type the new title."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:49
msgid "Save with the <i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i> button or Enter key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:51
msgid "To change the title of a document only in your CryptDrive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:52
msgid ""
"Right click on the document in your CryptDrive > <i class=\"fa fa-"
"pencil\"></i> Rename."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:53
msgid "Type the new name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:54
msgid "Save with the Enter key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:56
msgid ""
"The <i class=\"fa fa-flag\"></i> icon indicates that the title of a "
"document is different in your CryptDrive than for other users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:58
msgid "Deleting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:61
msgid "There are two ways of deleting a document on CryptPad:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:62
msgid ""
"<i class=\"fa fa-trash\"></i> Removing a document means it stops "
"appearing in the CryptDrive but remains in the database. The document "
"remains in the CryptDrive of other users who have stored it. The document"
" can be recovered in the CryptDrive using the [history]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:63
msgid ""
"<i class=\"cptools cptools-destroy\"></i> Destroying a document deletes "
"it from the database permanently. The document is deleted from all "
"CryptDrives that store it, and it cannot be recovered using the "
"CryptDrive history. {document owners}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:69
msgid "To remove a document from the CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:71
msgid ""
"Drag the document from the CryptDrive into the <i class=\"fa fa-"
"trash\"></i> Trash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:72
msgid "Right click > <i class=\"fa fa-trash\"></i> Move to trash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:73
msgid "Select the document and press the Del key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:75
msgid ""
"To remove the document from the CryptDrive without storing it in the "
"trash first:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:76
msgid "Select the document and press the Shift + Del keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:78
msgid "To empty the trash:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:79
msgid ""
"Right click on the <i class=\"fa fa-trash\"></i> Trash tab to the left of"
" the CryptDrive > <i class=\"fa fa-trash-o\"></i> Empty the trash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:80
msgid ""
"Click on the <i class=\"fa fa-trash\"></i> Trash tab to access the trash "
"> <i class=\"fa fa-trash-o\"></i> Empty the trash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:82
msgid ""
"If you are an [owner] of some documents in the trash when you empty it, "
"you are prompted to decide if you want to remove or destroy them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:84
msgid "To destroy a document without storing it in the trash first:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:87
msgid ""
"Right click on the document in the CryptDrive > <i class=\"cptools "
"cptools-destroy\"></i> Destroy. {document owners}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:91
msgid "CryptDrive history"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:95
msgid ""
"The CryptDrive history is saved and can be restored if needed. From the "
"CryptDrive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:97
msgid ""
"Click on the <i class=\"fa fa-history\"></i> history button at the top-"
"right (under the avatar)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:98
msgid ""
"Use the arrows <i class=\"fa fa-fast-backward\"></i> <i class=\"fa fa-"
"step-backward\"></i> to step through the history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:99
msgid ""
"Restore the current step with <i class=\"fa fa-check-circle-o\"></i>, or "
"exit the history wihtout restoring with <i class=\"fa fa-window-"
"close\"></i>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:101
msgid ""
"To save storage space the CryptDrive history can be deleted in the [user "
"settings]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:107
msgid "Tags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:110
msgid ""
"Group documents in multiple categories by using tags. Your tags are not "
"visible by other users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:112
msgid ""
"The <i class=\"fa fa-hashtag\"></i> Tags tab in the CryptDrive displays "
"all tags in use and their associated documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:114
msgid "To add or remove tags from a document:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:118
msgid ""
"From the CrytpDrive: Right click on the document > <i class=\"fa fa-"
"hashtag\"></i> Tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:119
msgid ""
"From a document: <i class=\"fa fa-file-o\"></i> File > <i class=\"fa fa-"
"hashtag\"></i> Tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:121
msgid "To manage tags for multiple documents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:122
msgid "Select the documents with Ctrl + Click in the CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:123
msgid "Right click on the documents > <i class=\"fa fa-hashtag\"></i> Tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:125
msgid ""
"Only the tags assigned to all the documents are then displayed. Any tags "
"added and/or removed are applied to all the selected documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:127
msgid "Templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:130
msgid ""
"Templates provide reusable starting points to create documents of a "
"similar structure, for example invoices, letterheads, reports, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:133
msgid "To create a template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:135
msgid ""
"Select the  <i class=\"cptools cptools-template\"></i> Templates tab in "
"the CryptDrive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:136
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-plus\"></i> New in the toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:138 ../../user_guide/drive.md:142
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:140
msgid ""
"In an existing document:  <i class=\"fa fa-file-o\"></i> File > <i "
"class=\"fa fa-bookmark\"></i> Save as template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:144
msgid "Create a [new document]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:145
msgid ""
"On the creation screen select <i class=\"cptools cptools-new-"
"template\"></i> New template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:147
msgid "To use a template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:149
msgid "Select the template when creating a [new document]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/drive.md:150
msgid ""
"In an existing document: <i class=\"fa fa-file-o\"></i> File > <i "
"class=\"fa fa-upload\"></i> Import a template.<br />Please note: this "
"option replaces the contents of the document with the template."
msgstr ""

